   <text>
      <body>
         <div>
            <pb facs="#facs_1" n="TLx-0008_p001.jpg" xml:id="img_0001" corresp="https://id.acdh.oeaw.ac.at/tillich-lectures/TLx-0008_p001.jpg"/>
            <p facs="#facs_1_r">
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l" n="N001"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">I GROUP</hi>
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_1" n="N002"/>1) <rs type="person" key="Ostade, tillich_person_id__3085"><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">OSTADE</hi></rs> {Rustic Couple Dancing} (vital ecstasy)
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_2" n="N003"/>[The Jubilee]
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_3" n="N004"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;"><rs type="person" key="Steen, tillich_person_id__3084">Jan Steen</rs>.</hi> The painter's family
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_4" n="N005"/>2) <rs type="person" key="Watteau, tillich_person_id__3086"><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">WATTEAU</hi></rs> {French Comedy}
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_5" n="N006"/>(Les comédiens Francais)
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_6" n="N007"/>(The comedian, later the harlekin, the
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_7" n="N008"/>[play as] Pierrot expression of vitality, {refined} [later tragic)]
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_8" n="N009"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">W:</hi> Love in Italian comedy
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_9" n="N010"/>3) <rs type="person" key="Renoir, tillich_person_id__1583"><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">RENOIR</hi></rs> {Breakfeast [sic.] by the River} (Chicago)
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_10" n="N011"/>Les Canotiers à Chatouse
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_11" n="N012"/>(The union of nature and society: The discovery
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_12" n="N013"/>of nature as life-power)
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_13" n="N014"/>4) <rs type="person" key="van Ruysdael, tillich_person_id__1667"><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">RUYSDAEL</hi></rs> {Ruins of Egmont (Chicago)}
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_14" n="N015"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">Jacob.</hi> Edge of a Wood
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_15" n="N016"/>(The power of nature itself. The tree and
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_16" n="N017"/>the power of treehood)
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_17" n="N018"/>5) <rs type="person" key="Monet, tillich_person_id__1343"><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">MONET</hi></rs> {Argenteuil (Chicago)}
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_18" n="N019"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">Claude</hi>, Waterloo Bridge, London
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_19" n="N020"/>(The positivistic stream of {nature} consciousness in
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_20" n="N021"/>the vision of the subject)
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_21" n="N022"/>6) <hi style="text-decoration: underline;"><rs type="person" key="Bronzino, tillich_person_id__3087">A. BRONZINO</rs> </hi>Portrait of {a Lady}
